metadata.name: Brosser #185
metadata.description:
Exploring generative brush strokes to simulate real life paintings. 

- A selection of 19 different palettes
- 4 different drawing styles
- Randomized "color swap" between the primary and secondary colors in each palette

Several other factors determine the output of a piece, including angles, depth, brush length, and brush weight, among others.

metadata.name: cc1: fairpass #99
metadata.description:
competitive coding settings have scope for creativity in problem solving, but the way outputs are expressed is largely reductive- where efficiency is the only thing that's rewarded

this piece is part of the "cc" series, that turns "competitive coding" problems of varying difficulty into "creatively coded" artworks using p5.js. it is an intervention within a largely mechanistic system, a system that has been time and again used as a differentiator of acumen, this an attempt to rethink what it means to write "good" code.

taking screenshots- press the up arrow key to save a pdf, and the down arrow key to save a png

metadata.name: Coronado #101
metadata.description:
This series is about the beauty and charm of imperfection, chaos amidst order, and letting go. It's about knowing that however much control we think we may have, things can all fall apart or burst into something unexpectedly wonderful at any moment, even without our hands tightly on the reigns.

Please see fxtext article linked from main project page for more background on the project and rendering notes.

Some key commands in live mode:

G : Toggle grain
S : Save current resolution
1 : 4000x5000
2 : 6000x7500
3 : 8000x10000
4 : 10000x12500
5 : 12000x15000
6 : 14000x17500
(1-6 work best on Chrome)
(rendering takes longer as resolution increases)

metadata.name: Swamp Garden Ecosystem #50
metadata.description:
The generated picture presents an ecosystem of swamp
garden wetlands and tadpoles in the water.

In live view mode:
- Press Key "a" to regenerate with scale x1.5 (2160x2160 px)
- Press Key "z" to regenerate with scale x2 (2880x2880 px)
- Press Key "e" to regenerate with scale x2.5 (3600x3600 px)
- Press Key "r" to regenerate with scale x3 (4320x4320 px)
- Press Key "t" to regenerate with scale x3.5 (5040x5040 px)

Press [p] to save captured image to png


Enjoy :)

---
Created using vanilla javascript
KrouniHatim - Nov22
---

metadata.name: Limitless imagination #164
metadata.description:
Limitless imagination is the result of transforming objects into subjects, we should not simply pass by simple objects. This collection consists of combining a hundred objects with each other and obtaining a thousand unique results.

The idea of this collection came to me when I was sitting under a glass corridor and the shadows of the passers-by above me were like ink blots that swallowed each other and created amazing images.
